      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely slice the <strong>brown onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced onion</strong> with a generous knob of <strong>butter alternative</strong>, a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong></p><p>Cook for 12-15 min or until golden and caramelised, then transfer them to a bowl and reserve the pan for later – these are your<strong> caramelised onions</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
